entry.title: Gowdy: The screw-up at The New York Times

media:group.media:title: Gowdy: The screw-up at The New York Times
media:group.media:description:
The Trey Gowdy Podcast | June 9, 2020 Get more episodes of The Trey Gowdy Podcast here: https://bit.ly/2L5gjcJ
Former Congressman Trey Gowdy speaks with Wall Street Journal editorial board member Kim Strassel.
Kim tells Trey about how she first discovered her passion for journalism. She breaks down the difference between news and editorials and how a newspaper decides what news is worth covering. She explains how young people can ensure the news they are reading is reliable and how newspapers choose conservative and liberal voices for their editorial boards. Trey and Kim also break down why the New York Times Opinion Editor's resignation over an unpopular op-ed may damage people's faith in journalism.
Later, Trey and Kim discuss her experience covering the Russia investigation in 2016 and the importance of journalists applying the same standard to everyone.
